text: Sarah Ulmer (born 24 April 1977 in Regina) is a Canadian rugby union player. She played for the Canada women's national rugby union team at the 2002 Women's Rugby World Cup, 2006 Women's Rugby World Cup, and 2010 Women's Rugby World Cup. == References == == Other websites == * https://www.scrumqueens.com/features/60-second-interview-sarah-ulmer Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian sportspeople Category:Rugby union players
